<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-15T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-15T20:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/10798b:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-15T21:00:00-04:00">May 15,
                                    1944—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>920. We suggest that you consult with Mallet with a view to calling on
                            your Soviet colleague,<note n="55" xml:id="d509fn1">Mme. Alexandra
                                Kollontay, Soviet Minister in Sweden.</note> if you have not already
                            done so, to inform her of the results of our negotiations to date with
                            respect to ball-bearing exports to the enemy in view of her Government’s
                            support of our <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> to the Swedes in that
                            connection.</p>
                        <p>Sent to Stockholm, repeated to Moscow for information.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>